  "description": "On Bike touring",
  "body_html": "<p>I\u2019m trying to save money to fund some of my experiments at home. </p><p>Instead of saving on small things (like skipping coffees at cafes), I\u2019ve realised that I can be more effective optimising on the big things. One big thing is holidays. Holidays cost a lot, and they form(ed) a huge part of my yearly expenditure. </p><p>The simplest solution to cut cost is to not go on holiday. That works to an extent. When I can, I try to spend my time off making things at home, instead of travelling. I think this works if you can find something you love so much that you don\u2019t need to take breaks. </p><p>But not going on holiday at all is unrealistic. So, I am trying to find a way to spend much less money, for the same amount of fun. </p><p>After a brief analysis, the two biggest costs from my holiday typically come from of transportation (flights), and accommodation. </p><p>So as a result, I\u2019ve been trying to figuring out how to go on holiday <em>without</em> transport and <em>without</em> accommodation. </p><p>One of the things that fit the bill is bike touring. Bike touring is when one takes a bike, packs a bunch of camping gear, food, and clothes, and rides around a route. If ride my bike locally in the UK (or in Europe via boat) with my tent on the back, then my transport costs would be around $100 round trip for ferry or train (and $0 if in the UK), and around $10 a night to stay at campsites. I think this is relatively cheap. This is what it looks like: </p><div class=\"captioned-image-container\"><figure><a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!nfCn!,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62e07d99-2782-410e-9eb5-28d7cb52655b_475x588.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"><div class=\"image2-inset\"><picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!nfCn!,w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62e07d99-2782-410e-9eb5-28d7cb52655b_475x588.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!nfCn!,w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62e07d99-2782-410e-9eb5-28d7cb52655b_475x588.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!nfCn!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62e07d99-2782-410e-9eb5-28d7cb52655b_475x588.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!nfCn!,w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62e07d99-2782-410e-9eb5-28d7cb52655b_475x588.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!nfCn!,w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62e07d99-2782-410e-9eb5-28d7cb52655b_475x588.png\" width=\"475\" height=\"588\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/62e07d99-2782-410e-9eb5-28d7cb52655b_475x588.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:588,&quot;width&quot;:475,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:645079,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://chillphysicsenjoyer.substack.com/i/173116563?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F62e07d99-2782-410e-9eb5-28d7cb52655b_475x588.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" srcset=\"